{"author":"Iso Tester","data":{"body":"[PLAN REVIEW · PASS 1 · G6 — Approach soundness, anti-patterns & alternative-selection]\n\nVERDICT: PASS (no findings). Reviewing the \"Migrate plan-review + completion-verification onto the workflow engine\" plan against G6, grounded in the live code.\n\nAFFIRMATIONS (criteria this chunk satisfies):\n\n1. MECHANISM CORRECTNESS — sound and complete. The plan's load-bearing mechanism is PLANNED-TRACE parity (control-flow shape) rather than result parity, correctly recognizing LLM output is non-deterministic and byte-comparison is incoherent. Grounded check confirms the mechanism works: the harness compares DET coverage on every scenario, finder traces (role + sorted criteria + call-mode + intended entry model, concurrency-order-normalized), and cross-asserts the verify call-mode (tests/unit/workflow/test_plan_review_parity.py; capture via src/rebar/llm/workflow/trace.py). Edge/empty/failure cases are handled: P1/P5 DET-block and P8-too-big/bug-exempt scenarios are explicitly partitioned in the corpus (tests/unit/workflow/_parity_corpus.py); the cutover (gate_dispatch.py) preserves INDETERMINATE-on-outage for plan-review and fail-closed-on-outage for completion, with signing wrappers untouched so signed verdicts stay byte-compatible (AC4).\n\n2. The PRE-ESCALATION tolerance is a deliberate, defensible gap — not a hidden assumption. Size-ladder escalation is runtime-token-dependent and cannot be reproduced offline; the plan states this tolerance explicitly and still pins the laddered-finder ENTRY model + the budget/shed coverage, which is where the routing/chunking/ladder complexity (the real safety surface) lives. No TOCTOU / ordering / atomicity defect found.\n\n3. FITNESS-FOR-PURPOSE — solves the named problem (one engine substrate, validated parity, samples removed), not a proxy. The \"model=None echo\" subtlety is correctly handled (capture the INTENDED/selected req.config.model, not the fake's echoed field) — trace.py confirms.\n\n4. APPROACH SELECTION — chosen approach is defensibly at-least-as-good as structurally-different alternatives I generated (result-parity/golden snapshots — rejected, incoherent for LLM gates; live shadow-traffic flag-flip — slower, costs tokens, not CI-able, can't exhaustively hit P1/P5/P8/exempt/overlay edges; incremental walking-skeleton-first — the plan in fact does this by migrating completion first). The offline-corpus design wins on testability, cost, CI-ability, and edge coverage. Discarding the alternatives (not writing them into the plan).\n\n5. POSITIVE RATIONALE present throughout (G6.4 satisfied): planned-trace because the review is LLM-variable; offline FakeRunner so edge cases are exhaustive/cheap/CI-able; extract sizing.py behind epic A's seam to avoid algorithm duplication; completion fits existing constructs (no new kinds needed). No rejected-alternatives section required (anti-priming respected).\n\nNo coaching findings for G6."},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"COMMENT","timestamp":1782507439683284001,"uuid":"eeb066ba-c054-40cc-b8f3-56236b36ddb4"}